
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-rosen-l3vpn-mvpn-bier-02.txt'>
    <title>"Multicast VPN Using BIER", Eric Rosen, Mahesh Sivakumar, IJsbrand Wijnands, Sam Aldrin, Andrew Dolganow, Tony Przygienda</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-rosen-l3vpn-mvpn-bier-02.txt</link>
    <description>The Multicast Virtual Private Network (MVPN) specifications require the use of multicast tunnels ("P-tunnels") that traverse a Service Provider's backbone network.  The P-tunnels are used for carrying multicast traffic across the backbone.  A variety of P-tunnel types are supported.  Bit Index Explicit Replication (BIER) is a new architecture that provides optimal multicast forwarding through a "multicast domain", without requiring intermediate routers to maintain any per-flow state or to engage in an explicit tree-building protocol.  This document specifies the protocol and procedures that allow MVPN to use BIER as the method of carrying multicast traffic over an SP backbone network.</description>
    <dc:date>2014-12-04T08:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
